{
  "stem": "12413.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then, on the loudspeaker, there were coming orders in rapid-- rapid orders, in German.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[SPEAKING GERMAN], which meant 'All  the Jews to the gate.' 'All the Jews to the gate.' No mention of French, Dutch, Poles, Hungarian, Romanian-- Jews.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because it was a big question.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I paid a visit in Buchenwald in 1991.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I didn't find-- I found all nationalities.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I didn't find gypsies-- Jews and gypsies.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I found American, English, Dutch, Norwegian, Spanish, Spaniards, Italian-- all nationalities.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "No Jews. 30,000 Jews were in Buchenwald between the end of 1944 till April 9-- 10, 1945, the last evacuation.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "To this very day, in the book of history-- and there are two excellent books-- and another book by Eugene Kogon, who died at age of 92-- and there isn't a mention about Jews.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "For the German, as a [INAUDIBLE] flash, as a cover-up, the Jews were Poles, Norwegians, but no Jews.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But I am pointing out again that, in this hospital, the window open, I heard this order with my ears, to the best of my ability-- there was no hallucinating.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I was already in better shape.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I saw a scene which I never forget in my life to the rest of my days-- thousands of people being herded by the SS, beaten, dragged, beaten-- beaten-- with German-- they used those German shepherds-- and being evacuated.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Between April 4th and April 10, the last day of evacuation, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] more than 20,000-- maybe 25,000 Jews-- were slaughtered-- in Buchenwald, on the road outside of Buchenwald, and on the death march-- death march from Buchenwald to Dachau.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My brother was among them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "This I learned later.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
